<h2>Cherry Services</h2>

<h6>
Cherry Services widget helps to display the services you provide in an attractive way. The widget showcases services using categories or ID. It provides full responsiveness and allows you to set featured images and description length for the services you offer.
</h6>

<h4>Content</h4>

 	<figure class="img-polaroid">
        <img src="projects/<?php echo $project;?>/img/widget/service2.png">
  	</figure>

<ul class="marked-list">
<p><li><b>Super Title</b>  — here you need to input the super title for Cherry Services widget. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Title</b>  — in this field you can fill in the title for Cherry Services. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Subtitle</b>  — here you need to define the subtitle to use for the widget. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Desktop Columns</b>  — here you need to define the number of columns in which the services information will be displayed for the desktop resolution. You can set from 1 to 6 columns per one line. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Laptop Columns</b>  — here you need to define the number of columns in which the services information will be displayed for the laptop resolution. You can set from 1 to 6 columns per one line. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Tablet Columns</b>  — here you need to define the number of columns in which the services information will be displayed for the tablet resolution. Try to reduce the number of columns to ensure the best responsiveness. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Phone Columns</b>  — here you need to define the number of columns in which the services information will be displayed for the phone screen resolution. Try to reduce the number of columns to ensure the best responsiveness. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Posts per Page</b>  — here you can define how many posts you want to display per one page. The maximum number of posts is 50. Set “0” value to display all the existing posts per one page. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show Services from Categories</b>  — here you can select the particular category of services you want to display in this widget. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show Services by ID</b>  — in this block you can input the ID number for the services you want to display in the widget. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Description Length</b>  — here you can define the length of the services description (set the number of words). Description maximum length is 200 words. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show More Button</b>  — here you can enable/disable More button and define button text and button URL. </li></p>
<p><li><b>AJAX Load More</b>  — here you can enable or disable AJAX Load More button. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Pagination</b>  — enable this option if you want to show pagination circles at the bottom of the widget to provide more comfortable navigation. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show Services Title</b>  — here you can define the title for the Services widget. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show Featured Image</b>  — here you can enable or disable featured images for the services. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show Service Content</b>  — here you can enable or disable displaying content for the services. </li></p>
<p><li><b>Show Filter by Category Before Services Listing</b>  — here you can enable services category links at the top of the widget.</li></p>
<p><li><b>Listing Item Image Size</b>  — here you can select the size of the images used in the widget (large, medium, small or thumbnail). </li></p>
<p><li><b>Listing Item Template</b>  — here you can define the listing type you want to use for the widget. It can be default, media—icon or media—icon—float. </li></p></ul>
<p>You can also add space between Services columns and rows using the corresponding options. </p>

